==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Papboat
<hw>Pap"boat`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind
of sauce boat or dish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large spiral East Indian marine
shell (<spn>Turbinella rapha</spn>); -- so called because used by native
priests to hold the oil for anointing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pape</ent>⟦br⟧
